<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Naming">Naming</h3><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DTablespoon&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Naming"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In recipes, an abbreviation like <i>tbsp.</i> is usually used to refer t=
o a tablespoon, to differentiate it from the smaller teaspoon (<i>tsp.</i>)=
.  Some authors capitalize the abbreviation, as  <i>Tbsp.</i>, while leavin=
g <i>tsp.</i> in lower case, to emphasize that the larger tablespoon, rathe=
r than the smaller teaspoon, is wanted. The tablespoon abbreviation is some=
times abbreviated to <i>Tb.</i> or <i>T</i>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Traditional_definitions">Tr=
aditional definitions</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DTablespoon&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit secti=
on: Traditional definitions"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsec=
tion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In most places, one tablespoon equals three <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Teaspoon" title=3D"Teaspoon">teaspoons</a>.  In Australia and =
the UK, one tablespoon equals four teaspoons.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"International_metric">Inter=
national metric</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DTablespoon&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: In=
ternational metric"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">]</span></span></div>
<p>An international metric tablespoon is exactly equal to 15&nbsp;mL.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-:0_7-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Tablespoon#cite_note-:0-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  It is the equivalence of 1<s=
pan class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</sp=
an><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span>=E2=
=81=A0</span> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dessert_spoon#Culina=
ry_measure" title=3D"Dessert spoon">metric dessert spoons</a> or 3 <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teaspoon#Metric_teaspoon" title=3D"Teaspo=
on">metric teaspoons</a>.
</p>
